title: SD Trooper Attacked During Traffic Stop
text:
SD Trooper Attacked During Traffic Stop October 24, 2015, 3:47 PM PIERRE, SD - 
A South Dakota Highway Patrol trooper was assaulted during a traffic stop Saturday. 
The trooper stopped a vehicle near mile marker 70 near Rapid City around 11 a.m Saturday. During the traffic stop, the trooper was attacked and received serious non-life threatening injuries. 
The vehicle fled the scene but was later stopped by Pennington County deputies near Wall, SD. Four suspects were arrested. 
Pennington County authorities continue to investigate.
